Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them
onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the garlic, @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%grams},
@Mixed Herbs{1%sachet}, @Salt{¼%tsp} and @Water{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs,
then add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}. Season with @pepper{} and mix
together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a medium baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your
oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

In the meantime, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}. Halve the
@Burger Buns{2}(halved).

Once the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers
and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, pop the burger buns into the oven until warmed through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

When the wedges are cooked, sprinkle over the @Chilli Flakes{1%pinch} (add less
if you'd prefer things milder) and drizzle over the @Honey{1%tbsp}.

> See pantry for honey amount.

Toss to coat and return to the oven for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

When everything's ready, spread the @Mayonnaise{1%tbsp} over the bun bases and
the @Burger Sauce{45%grams} over the lids. Top the bases with the
cheeseburgers and some @Baby Leaf Mix{20%grams}, then sandwich shut with the
bun lids.

Serve your burgers with the hot honey wedges and any remaining baby leaves
alongside.

Enjoy!